1
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:39,333
<i>You're no longer allowed
near my husband.</i>

2
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,333
<i>Take advantage
while you still can.</i>

3
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:44,533
<i>Because my lawyer is already
filing a restraining order</i>

4
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:45,867
<i> against you.</i>

5
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,067
<i> Manuel is improving.</i>

6
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,200
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

7
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:49,467
<i> Doctor, where's Felma?</i>

8
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:50,767
<i> Felma's busy.</i>

9
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:54,100
<i>She's helping the people
Andrea scammed.</i>

10
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:55,500
<i> Dad's okay now, Mom.</i>

11
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:57,033
<i> We'll come by later.</i>

12
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:58,833
<i>But isn't there
a restraining order?</i>

13
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:02,867
<i>If I have to make
Jessica my ally, I will.</i>

14
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:07,233
<i>I don't know how I'll sneak
Aunt Felma into the ICU.</i>

15
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,233
<i> I'll go in again myself.</i>

16
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:12,100
<i> Mom.</i>

17
00:01:12,233 --> 00:01:14,200
<i>Who do you think you are,
ordering my daughter around?</i>

18
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:15,667
<i>- Let go of me, Jessica!
- Mom, no!</i>

19
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,100
<i>You're not getting
near him again!</i>

20
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:19,700
<i> Andrea!</i>

21
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:21,200
<i>- Mom, no!
- Andrea!</i>

22
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,300
<i>- Mom, no!
- Let me go!</i>

23
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:24,933
<i> Andrea, you have to know!</i>

24
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:26,767
<i>Jessica isn't your
father's daughter!</i>

25
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:27,600
<i>- You're not sisters!
- No!</i>

26
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:29,600
<i> Mom! Mom! No!</i>

27
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:31,867
<i>Discharge Against
Medical Advice?</i>

28
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,300
<i>You're taking Manuel home
already?</i>

29
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:34,800
<i> Doctor, I can handle it.</i>

30
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:35,800
<i> All right.</i>

31
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:36,800
<i> We'll get this done.</i>

32
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,233
<i> Thank you, Doc.</i>

33
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:46,867
Yes, Mom.

34
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,900
Just please don't come here yet.

35
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:49,967
Things are still tense.

36
00:01:51,367 --> 00:01:52,067
Okay.

37
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:57,533
Andrea, good news.

38
00:01:57,667 --> 00:01:59,967
The doctor came by earlier.

39
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,867
I can be discharged later.

40
00:02:05,433 --> 00:02:06,167
Why?

41
00:02:08,567 --> 00:02:09,867
It's Jessica.

42
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:14,167
Hazel caught us.

43
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:22,833
Hazel's going to hurt Jessica
again...

44
00:02:22,967 --> 00:02:24,300
because of me.

45
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,900
I can't do anything to help her.

46
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:36,267
Poor Jessica.

47
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:42,933
My poor sister.

48
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:50,500
Hush now.

49
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:10,800
Dear, is it true that your Mom
told Andrea to come

50
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:12,667
when I was still unconscious?

51
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:16,167
Not just Felma?

52
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:21,167
Yes, Dad.

53
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:24,400
She asked me to let Andrea in.

54
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:26,667
She said next time,

55
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,033
everyone can come
once you're out of the ICU.

56
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:35,667
What? Did your mom really
change?

57
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,100
Or is she just pretending?

58
00:03:39,067 --> 00:03:41,133
Yes, Dad. She's changed.

59
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:45,900
I'll finally see them all again.

60
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:47,667
We'll all be together.

61
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,133
Love you, Dad.

62
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:56,900
Love you too, sweetie.

63
00:03:59,567 --> 00:04:00,833
So much.

64
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:33,233
Mom.

65
00:04:35,867 --> 00:04:36,467
Hey.

66
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,333
Can I sleep with you?

67
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:41,667
Come here, sweetheart.

68
00:04:49,133 --> 00:04:50,067
Come.

69
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:57,833
Oh, why are you here?

70
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,767
Where's Joel?

71
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,567
Brix is with him, Mom.

72
00:05:03,733 --> 00:05:07,200
I'll go tomorrow once
Joel's discharged.

73
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:19,800
What's going on here?
Why is everyone crowding in?

74
00:05:19,933 --> 00:05:21,333
We came to be with you.

75
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:25,667
Move over.

76
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,967
Move, move, move!

77
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,767
Thank you, my children.

78
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:36,233
Thank you.

79
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,367
Mom...

80
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:47,700
Can't we really go
near Dad anymore?

81
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:59,300
No.

82
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:02,800
This can't go on.

83
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:05,000
It can't.

84
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:06,633
I won't let it.

85
00:06:08,967 --> 00:06:10,667
I'll be fine if I don't
see him...

86
00:06:14,067 --> 00:06:16,600
but not you, my kids.

87
00:06:17,733 --> 00:06:19,233
Not you.

88
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:23,600
You have to see your father.

89
00:06:23,733 --> 00:06:25,900
Because you have the right.

90
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:31,667
But what do we do, Mom?

91
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:37,000
Hazel keeps insisting
the legalities.

92
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:40,433
She said they're the only ones
with legal rights to Dad.

93
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,800
We have none.

94
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:50,333
I'm the only one without
any legal right to your father.

95
00:06:52,800 --> 00:07:00,033
Kids, tomorrow you'll
go to the hospital.

96
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:03,400
Bring your birth certificates.

97
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:10,500
Show Hazel your
father's signature.

98
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,700
Your father's signature.

99
00:07:15,567 --> 00:07:18,600
You have rights, my children.

100
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:21,133
Yeah, that's right.

101
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:22,733
I'm sorry.

102
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:27,567
It only came to me now.

103
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:32,767
A great deal has
happened in my life.

104
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:35,800
I'm sorry, my kids.

105
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:37,400
I'm sorry.

106
00:07:38,867 --> 00:07:40,733
I'm really sorry.

107
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,800
We'll fight.

108
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,467
We'll fight this.

109
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:54,467
We'll fight!

110
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,733
We'll fight, okay?

111
00:07:56,867 --> 00:07:57,767
We'll fight.

112
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:58,733
That's enough.

113
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:02,533
Hey, I told you.

114
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:04,067
Take care of that wound, okay?

115
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,600
No workouts at the condo
for now.

116
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:07,933
Yes, of course.

117
00:08:08,067 --> 00:08:09,300
I promise.

118
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:11,233
And stop insisting
on bringing me home.

119
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:12,567
Brix will meet me there anyway.

120
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:16,433
You think I'll just let you
ridea car alone?

121
00:08:16,567 --> 00:08:17,467
No way.

122
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,267
Jeffrey and Coleen are
coming later, it's fine.

123
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,333
Jessica?

124
00:08:28,567 --> 00:08:29,433
Andrea?

125
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:33,000
Careful, okay? Go ahead.

126
00:08:33,133 --> 00:08:35,533
Wait. Jessica, where are you
going?

127
00:08:35,667 --> 00:08:36,900
Help me with this.

128
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:38,167
Go ahead.

129
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,667
- Jessica, hold it.
- Dad?

130
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,367
Where are you taking my father?

131
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:45,367
Hurry! We'll get stuck
in traffic!

132
00:08:45,533 --> 00:08:46,100
No!

133
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:46,967
Hazel!

134
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:47,967
Where are you taking my father?

135
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,700
- Let go of me!
- Bring him back!

136
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:50,367
Let my dad out!

137
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,200
Bring him back!

138
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:55,300
- Let go of me!
- Bring him back!

139
00:08:55,467 --> 00:08:56,267
- There!
- Hurry up!

140
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,733
- Andrea!
- Hurry up!

141
00:08:58,867 --> 00:08:59,967
- Wait!
- What happened?

142
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,033
Wait, Mister!

143
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:02,333
- Quick!
- Open this door!

144
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:03,333
Hazel!

145
00:09:03,467 --> 00:09:04,967
- What happened?
- Open it!

146
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,400
Wait!

147
00:09:07,533 --> 00:09:08,467
Wait!

148
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,900
Dad!

149
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:14,233
Dad!

150
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:34,300
Mom's taking forever
to get dressed.

151
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:36,600
Of course. She's fixing up
for Dad.

152
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:39,767
Oh, we're still hoping
they'll get back together.

153
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,333
They're not even at
the sweet stage yet.

154
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:44,100
Clarify that, Andrea?

155
00:09:44,233 --> 00:09:45,767
Hazel took Manuel out?

156
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,900
Where's she taking him?

157
00:09:49,033 --> 00:09:50,700
I don't know, Mom.

158
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:52,467
I don't know.

159
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,167
Find out, Andrea!

160
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:56,467
Find out!

161
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,767
No one here knows
anything, Mom.

162
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,633
I don't even know
how Dad is right now.

163
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:04,833
I haven't seen him.

164
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:07,233
I haven't even hugged him.

165
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:09,967
I haven't even hugged my father
yet.

166
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:12,000
Mom, what's happening?

167
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:15,033
Hazel took your father!

168
00:10:15,167 --> 00:10:17,500
- What?
- She took your father!

169
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,733
Hazel!

170
00:10:21,867 --> 00:10:22,567
Mom.

171
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:46,867
Where did you take Manuel?

172
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,933
You're a monster!

173
00:10:48,067 --> 00:10:50,300
You're a monster, Hazel!

174
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:52,067
You're a monster!

175
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,667
Mom, please stop!

176
00:10:53,800 --> 00:11:00,600
You monster!

177
00:11:00,733 --> 00:11:02,933
You're a monster, Hazel!

178
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,900
Manuel!

179
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:11,533
Where did you take Manuel?

180
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:14,267
Where did you take Manuel?

181
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:28,433
Mommy, are you sure
this is safe?

182
00:11:28,567 --> 00:11:29,800
Stop worrying.

183
00:11:29,933 --> 00:11:31,500
I know what I'm doing.

184
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:32,733
Why do you think I became
a nurse

185
00:11:32,867 --> 00:11:35,767
if I can't even take care
of your dad?

186
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,767
But Mom, what if his
condition worsens?

187
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:40,333
It's still different if
Dad's in the hospital.

188
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:42,600
Jessica, are you
doubting my ability?

189
00:11:42,767 --> 00:11:43,867
Are you belittling me?

190
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,767
Mom, that's not what I meant.

191
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,400
Then what?

192
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:49,267
You'd rather your dad stay
in the hospital,

193
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,567
where that Felma and her
illegitimate kids can visit him?

194
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:56,633
I'm just scared to lose Dad.

195
00:11:56,767 --> 00:11:59,400
Me too. I'm scared too.

196
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:03,000
That's why I'll do everything
so I won't lose your dad.

197
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:04,300
So we won't lose him.

198
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:05,833
Don't worry.

199
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:08,533
Nothing bad will happen
to your dad, okay?

200
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:09,700
I'll make sure of that.

201
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:20,433
Wait!

202
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:21,867
Wait! Let me in!

203
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:22,867
Wait!

204
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:27,533
Why did you let Hazel
take Manuel out?

205
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:31,433
It's only been days
since his surgery!

206
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:35,500
Ma'am, we only followed
the patient's request.

207
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:38,700
He signed a Discharge
Against Medical Advice.

208
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:43,200
Did Manuel signed it?

209
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:45,167
Yes, Ma'am.

210
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,233
Why didn't you inform us?

211
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:48,767
Sir, I'm sorry,

212
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:52,367
but we coordinated with
Mrs. Cruz, the legal wife.

213
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:56,367
If there's any information
you need,

214
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,200
it has to come from her.

215
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:00,200
But she never told us anything!

216
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:01,767
Again, I'm really sorry,

217
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:05,267
but I don't think this is
any of our concern.

218
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,133
Where did Hazel take Manuel?

219
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:11,667
Sorry, Ma'am, but we don't know.

220
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:15,600
You let my father leave
without informing us,

221
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:18,467
and now you don't even know
where they went?

222
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:21,233
We'll sue this hospital!

223
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,933
Coleen, don't.

224
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:24,633
Wait, wait.

225
00:13:24,767 --> 00:13:28,067
Let's clear things up,
all right?

226
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:31,533
We have no obligation to
give you the information

227
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:32,633
you're asking for.

228
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:37,333
Our contact is the legal wife,
Mrs. Cruz, okay?

229
00:13:37,467 --> 00:13:38,767
You'll sue us?

230
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,433
On what grounds?

231
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:42,000
Maybe we should be the
ones suing you

232
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:44,233
for everything you've done.

233
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:46,600
Look, if you have issues
with Mrs. Cruz,

234
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:47,933
that's between you and her.

235
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:51,233
Fight her all you want,
I don't care.

236
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:53,700
But don't you dare drag
this hospital into it!

237
00:13:56,567 --> 00:13:58,733
Come on, dear. Let's go.

238
00:13:58,867 --> 00:13:59,533
- Nurse Miles.
- This conversation's

239
00:13:59,667 --> 00:14:01,733
going nowhere.

240
00:14:01,867 --> 00:14:02,933
Nurse Alice,
please come in.

241
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:04,633
You may leave, Miss.

242
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:10,200
Where did Hazel take Manuel?

243
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:11,133
I don't know.

244
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:26,700
That's impossible!

245
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:27,633
Mom!

246
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,400
- You're in cahoots with Hazel!
- Ouch.

247
00:14:29,533 --> 00:14:31,233
Tell me where she is!

248
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:32,267
I told you, I don't know!

249
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,300
Tell me!

250
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:35,067
- Tell me!
- Mom, stop!

251
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,033
- That's enough!
- Enough, Mom.

252
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:39,333
- Mom, stop!
- Please get out of my room.

253
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:42,033
If not, I'll call the
police right now!

254
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:43,600
Leave. Now!

255
00:14:43,733 --> 00:14:44,200
Mom, come on.

256
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:45,667
- Mom.
- Let's go.

257
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,600
Let's talk outside.

258
00:14:46,733 --> 00:14:47,967
Come on.

259
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,833
Come on, Mom.

260
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,433
You're such a ghoster, Brix.

261
00:14:54,567 --> 00:14:57,100
You said you'd be here
when I arrived!

262
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:58,467
Kidding, kidding.

263
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,267
It's fine, I'm settled now.

264
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,033
You can come.

265
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,500
Okay. Bye.

266
00:15:05,667 --> 00:15:07,067
You know,

267
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,900
you can go ahead.

268
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:11,067
Your family needs you. Go on.

269
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,233
I'm fine.

270
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:15,367
No, Joel.

271
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:18,333
I can't just leave you.
You need me. Look at your wound.

272
00:15:18,467 --> 00:15:20,467
Andrea, if I need anything,

273
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,300
I'll call Lilet.

274
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:25,767
And Brix is on his way.
He just made a stop. Go on.

275
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,100
But Joel,

276
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:29,333
- I can't just leave you alone.
- Come on. Andrea...

277
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,167
your mom...

278
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,867
and siblings need you.

279
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:36,367
Put them first.

280
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:39,000
I'll be okay. It's not like
I'm babying this wound.

281
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:39,933
Go.

282
00:15:40,067 --> 00:15:42,667
Joel, I still can't
just leave you.

283
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,500
It's fine. I'll be okay.

284
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:46,300
Take care.

285
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:48,767
- You sure?
- Yes.

286
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:49,733
Of course.

287
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:52,000
Stay with them, okay?

288
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,633
Tom,

289
00:16:06,767 --> 00:16:07,900
Kenjie,

290
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,633
thank you.

291
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:11,100
Wait for me downstairs.

292
00:16:11,233 --> 00:16:12,933
We still need to talk.

293
00:16:42,667 --> 00:16:44,400
Mommy, what's that?

294
00:16:44,533 --> 00:16:47,100
Something to help
your dad sleep longer.

295
00:16:47,233 --> 00:16:49,400
He needs plenty of rest.

296
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,500
Manuel,

297
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:04,367
this is the start of our new
life.

298
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,800
I'll make it up to you.

299
00:17:09,367 --> 00:17:10,633
I'll never let you go again.

300
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,633
And I won't let anyone...

301
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,433
tear this family apart.

302
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:19,767
I won't stop, Manuel.

303
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,333
Not until you
learn to love me.

304
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,233
Until...

305
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:29,767
I'm the only one you love.

306
00:17:35,667 --> 00:17:38,600
That Hazel is a monster.

307
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:40,700
Such a monster.

308
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:41,800
Mom?

309
00:17:46,167 --> 00:17:47,833
Mom! Mom!

310
00:17:49,567 --> 00:17:50,767
Mom!

311
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:53,067
We got nothing.

312
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,367
They said they don't know
where Hazel took Dad.

313
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:03,500
Mom, I want to talk to Dad.

314
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:11,600
I haven't even asked
for his forgiveness yet.

315
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:14,700
He doesn't know
I've already forgiven him.

316
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,600
Mom, let's find him.

317
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:18,067
Please.

318
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,500
But how, sis?

319
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:27,967
Jessica's with them,
but she won't answer my calls.

320
00:18:29,433 --> 00:18:30,733
You, Mom.

321
00:18:30,867 --> 00:18:34,233
She might pick up
if you call her.

322
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:37,267
Are we still trusting that brat?

323
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:41,100
Isn't it obvious
she's conniving with her mother?

324
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:43,300
This is what I've been telling
you all along!

325
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:45,233
You never believe me.

326
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:48,833
Mom, can I borrow
your phone?

327
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:10,900
I'm sorry, Aunt Felma.

328
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:15,533
I really am.

329
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:24,033
<i>I'm the product
of my parents' sin against you,</i>

330
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:26,700
<i>and still, you were kind to me.</i>

331
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:29,933
<i>You never made me
feel your anger.</i>

332
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,833
<i> Thank you, Miss Felma.</i>

333
00:19:37,567 --> 00:19:38,833
Aunt Felma.

334
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:41,700
Jessica?

335
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,400
Jessica, where are you?

336
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:44,833
Where did you take Dad?

337
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:49,100
Jessica, sweetheart.
We're worried.

338
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:53,833
Hazel shouldn't have taken
Manuel out of the hospital.

339
00:19:53,967 --> 00:19:57,533
Jessica, please tell us.

340
00:19:57,667 --> 00:19:59,433
Where are you?

341
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,567
Jessica, where are you?

342
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:08,033
Hello?

343
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:09,933
Jessica.

344
00:20:10,067 --> 00:20:12,600
Mom. Mom.

345
00:20:12,733 --> 00:20:14,200
You just don't know
how to follow, do you?

346
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:16,633
Mom, they're just worried
about Dad.

347
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:21,633
Mom, they're just worried about
Dad.

348
00:20:29,133 --> 00:20:30,533
Mom, she's gone.

349
00:20:32,667 --> 00:20:34,400
Wait, let me call her again.

350
00:20:44,967 --> 00:20:46,833
She's not answering anymore.

351
00:20:48,567 --> 00:20:50,533
What was that?
She just gave us false hope?

352
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:52,267
Then why did
she even pick up earlier?

353
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:55,967
For sure, her mom told her
to answer and give us hope.

354
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:57,633
To play with us.

355
00:20:57,767 --> 00:21:00,567
Now do you believe me?

356
00:21:00,700 --> 00:21:02,267
Jessica's in on it.

357
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,700
She's her mother's puppet.

358
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:06,600
My dear...

359
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:10,433
Jessica wouldn't play
with me like that.

360
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:11,900
Mom...

361
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:14,167
Then what do you call
what she did?

362
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:19,100
Mom, please, stop defending her.

363
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:22,900
You don't know what's
happening to her.

364
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:26,033
Didn't you hear
the fear in her voice?

365
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:28,233
Exactly.

366
00:21:30,467 --> 00:21:32,133
Maybe Hazel caught her.

367
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,467
Coleen, you're being
too harsh on Jessica.

368
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:39,600
You twist everything she does.
That's not right.

369
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:45,667
Don't be so negative
toward Jessica.

370
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,300
She's still our sister.

371
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:51,333
Dear...

372
00:21:52,933 --> 00:21:54,367
please.

373
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:32,000
Excuse me.

374
00:22:33,467 --> 00:22:35,467
May I ask something?

375
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:37,567
What is it?

376
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:38,633
I'll go ahead.

377
00:22:38,767 --> 00:22:40,433
Okay. Come back later.

378
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:45,467
Ma'am, where am I?

379
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,100
This is Camalig, dear.

380
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:48,967
Here, is Meycauayan.

381
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:53,100
Relax, okay? What's going on?
You seem lost.

382
00:22:53,233 --> 00:22:54,400
Jessica.

383
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:55,533
Oh, there you are, sweetie.

384
00:22:55,667 --> 00:22:57,033
I've been looking
all over for you.

385
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:58,800
Excuse us.

386
00:22:58,933 --> 00:23:00,267
Hazel!

387
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,100
Is that you, dear? Oh my!

388
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:03,433
It's me, Aunt Nita.

389
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:05,633
Your mother's
childhood friend!

390
00:23:07,067 --> 00:23:08,700
- Aunt Nita.
- Is it really you?

391
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:09,633
Bless me.

392
00:23:09,767 --> 00:23:11,500
How have you been?

393
00:23:11,633 --> 00:23:13,767
Still strong, thank God.

394
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:16,533
The last time I saw you,
you were just a young lady.

395
00:23:16,667 --> 00:23:18,600
Look at you now!

396
00:23:18,733 --> 00:23:19,967
I'm glad you came to visit.

397
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:21,967
Just here for vacation.

398
00:23:22,133 --> 00:23:25,133
I was thinking of having
our old house fixed.

399
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:27,667
But we'll catch up
some other time, okay?

400
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:28,800
I'll come visit you there.

401
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:30,033
We'll get going now.
We still have things to do.

402
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:31,700
Alright, alright.
Come back, okay?

403
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:32,833
I will.

404
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:43,667
I'm sorry if I hurt you again.

405
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,167
But Jessica,

406
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:49,267
what's wrong?

407
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:54,033
We already got your dad back.

408
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:55,533
Isn't that enough
to make you happy?

409
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:58,900
How can I be happy, Mom?

410
00:23:59,033 --> 00:24:00,633
You're treating us
like prisoners.

411
00:24:00,767 --> 00:24:03,767
You don't even think
about Dad's safety!

412
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:05,900
Stop ranting!

413
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:08,200
I'm not keeping
you prisoner.

414
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:10,133
I'm rebuilding our family!

415
00:24:10,267 --> 00:24:12,800
Why is it so hard
for you to understand that?

416
00:24:15,167 --> 00:24:17,300
You're smart, Jessica.

417
00:24:17,433 --> 00:24:19,433
I don't know what
happened to you.

418
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:22,567
Did your brain melt while
you were living with Felma?

419
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:26,467
What do you want?

420
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:28,367
For your dad to go back to them?

421
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:30,500
For their family
to be whole again?

422
00:24:30,667 --> 00:24:34,033
And you, they'll turn you
into an illegitimate child.

423
00:24:34,167 --> 00:24:35,400
Is that what you want?

424
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:41,600
Well, it's true.

425
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:46,633
Manuel isn't your real father.

426
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,700
So go ahead.

427
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:53,300
Tell them where we are.

428
00:24:54,633 --> 00:24:56,867
But I can't guarantee you...

429
00:24:57,000 --> 00:25:00,000
that Manuel and I will still
be here when they come.

430
00:25:03,867 --> 00:25:05,600
I just want to remind you,
Jessica.

431
00:25:07,067 --> 00:25:09,400
Your father's life
is in my hands.

432
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:11,900
So don't make me angry.

433
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:15,433
Because when I lose control,

434
00:25:17,367 --> 00:25:18,467
I don't know...

435
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:22,000
what I might do. I could give
him the wrong medicine.

436
00:25:23,733 --> 00:25:25,833
Mommy, are you serious?

437
00:25:26,967 --> 00:25:27,833
Mom.

438
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,333
Yes.

439
00:25:31,467 --> 00:25:34,067
If I can't have Manuel,
then no one will.

440
00:25:37,067 --> 00:25:40,067
So if you want your dad
to live and recover...

441
00:25:41,833 --> 00:25:43,100
you'll obey me.

442
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:45,867
Or else...

443
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,967
you'll regret it
for the rest of your life.

444
00:26:03,167 --> 00:26:06,500
The hospital's getting
dragged into your personal mess.

445
00:26:06,633 --> 00:26:07,500
Relax, Miles.

446
00:26:07,633 --> 00:26:10,200
I'm resigning
effective immediately.

447
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:11,167
Mom, why?

448
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:12,800
What happened? Is it Dad?

449
00:26:12,933 --> 00:26:13,833
No.

450
00:26:13,967 --> 00:26:16,033
Your brother's at the precinct.

451
00:26:16,167 --> 00:26:17,833
Hazel had him detained.

452
00:26:17,967 --> 00:26:18,800
What?

453
00:26:18,933 --> 00:26:20,500
Dad, do you need anything?

454
00:26:20,633 --> 00:26:21,800
- Food?
- Where am I?

455
00:26:21,933 --> 00:26:24,000
We're at Mom's old house.

456
00:26:24,133 --> 00:26:26,167
Does your Aunt Felma know?
